review_blob: Overall, Blue Moon.  MMM.  I do quite enjoy the stuff, you know.  Brings on a buzz fairly quick and nicely.  Nice wheats grainy taste, ice cold.  Get yourself a a big 12 and enjoy. From the bottles.

Fine beer, not the best by far.  Nice thick taste.  Better than a light. Itll buzz ya real nice.  One of my choice cases for a get together.  All in all, nice.  Watch how many you down, drink responsibly! I know I didnt the first go through. Nice drunk also. I really like some coors anyway.  Its a go getter, in my opinion.  Cheap enough.

Appears nicely, love the bottle, some may say that they dont enjoy the smell, but to me its just honeyish alcohol. It flows well, brings a nice buzz (like all others) So, what Im getting at , just enjoy, nice favors thrown in.  All all in I enjoyed, Im not much of a wine drinker, prefer heavies or liquor, but this wine was sort of a delicacy. The price is veeery reasonable.  It is good.  Not 1 million dollar fly fly fine wine, but, yes, nice buzz, nice tase, it flows.  Thanks guys, enjoy.
